Kudrin Sees Income Boost in Gas Tax, Interfax Says

-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 
2011-05-26T16:59:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/kudrin-sees-high-energy-tax-boosting-state-income-interfax-says.html
(Corrects headline and first paragraph to show tax increase
refers to gas extraction after Interfax corrects original report
following  Finance Ministry  clarification.)  Russian Finance Minister Alexei
Kudrin said raising the gas extraction tax is the only way to
boost budget revenue at the moment, Interfax reported.  The Finance Ministry proposes linking spending increases in
2012 and 2013 with economic growth in the period, Kudrin was
cited as saying by Interfax today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Shiryaevskaya in Moscow at 
 ashiryaevska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Abelsky at 
 pabelsky@bloomberg.net  